        <num>CHC 1015.1</num>
        <heading>1015.1.  Grounds; termination of parental rights of perpetrator of a sex offense</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1015.1.  Grounds; termination of parental rights of perpetrator of a sex offense
Parental rights of a natural parent may be terminated in cases where there is a
conviction or commission of a sex offense as defined in R.S. 15:541 by that natural parent
which resulted in the conception of the child.</p>
        </content>
